d internationally recognized for its scholarship in all fields — from fine arts to technology, humanities to life sciences, and music to entrepreneurship. UNT is committed to the creation and advancement of innovative research, art and scholarship. One of the primary responsibilities of the Office of Research and Innovation is to develop and implement strategies in collaboration with the Office of the Provost and other vice presidential areas to transform and expand UNT's research enterprise. Learn more about the Office of Research and Innovation » Sign up to receive our monthly enewsletter to learn about our research initiatives » Office of Research and Innovation Office of Grants & Contracts Administration Research Integrity & Compliance ORI-supported Intramural Grants & Awards Innovation and Commercialization Our Research Preserving the fabric of a nation A UNT researcher is developing digital technology to detect flaws in fabric at domestic textile mills – saving companies time and money. Helping visually impaired students learn computer science Using her understanding of what difficulties middle and high school students with visual impairments face when studying computing, she created curriculum and tools to help them overcome the obstacles. What we've learned from the Gulf oil spill If the parents of fish are exposed to oil, the next generation has an increased resistance to oil. However, this resistance may only last a few generations and go away when all the spilled oil is finally gone.  More research projects » Tools for Researchers The Office of Research supports new knowledge and its dissemination by assisting faculty in their research, scholarly, and creative activities. Strategic plans Forms IRB How to apply for a grant News & Honors Doctoral student/veteran awarded National Science Foundation Fellowship April 25, 2017 TAMS student wins Goldwater Scholarship April 24, 2017 Advancing genetic research April 14, 2017 Partnership helping to expand support f